  match n with
  | O => match m with
         | O => true
         | S m' => false
         end
  | S n' => match m with
            | O => false
            | S m' => eqb n' m'

  end.

Fixpoint leb (n m : nat) : bool :=
  match n with
  | O => true
  | S n' =>
      match m with
      | O => false
      | S m' => leb n' m'
      end
  end.

Definition letter_comparison (l1 l2 : letter) : comparison :=
  match l1, l2 with
  | A, A => Eq
  | A, _ => Gt
  | B, A => Lt
  | B, B => Eq
  | B, _ => Gt
  | C, (A | B) => Lt
  | C, C => Eq
  | C, _ => Gt
  | D, (A | B | C) => Lt
  | D, D => Eq
  | D, _ => Gt
  | F, (A | B | C | D) => Lt
  | F, F => Eq
  end.

  | Natural, _ => Gt
  | Minus, (Plus | Natural) => Lt

Definition apply_late_policy (late_days : nat) (g : grade) : grade :=
  if late_days <? 9 then g
  else if late_days <? 17 then lower_grade g
  else if late_days <? 21 then lower_grade (lower_grade g)
  else lower_grade (lower_grade (lower_grade g)).
Label: apply_late_policy

raw:
Theorem apply_late_policy_unfold :
  forall (late_days : nat) (g : grade),
    (apply_late_policy late_days g)
    =
    (if late_days <? 9 then g  else
       if late_days <? 17 then lower_grade g
       else if late_days <? 21 then lower_grade (lower_grade g)
            else lower_grade (lower_grade (lower_grade g))).
Proof.
  intros.
reflexivity.
Qed.
Label: apply_late_policy_unfold

raw:
Theorem no_penalty_for_mostly_on_time :
  forall (late_days : nat) (g : grade),
    (late_days <? 9 = true) ->
    apply_late_policy late_days g = g.
Proof.
   Admitted.
Label: no_penalty_for_mostly_on_time

raw:
Theorem grade_lowered_once :
  forall (late_days : nat) (g : grade),
    (late_days <? 9 = false) ->
    (late_days <? 17 = true) ->
    (apply_late_policy late_days g) = (lower_grade g).
Proof.
   Admitted.
Label: grade_lowered_once

  | nil => None

  | Chf_odd (n : nat) :  even n = false ->
                         Collatz_holds_for ((3 * n) + 1) ->
                         Collatz_holds_for n.

Inductive exp_match {T} : list T -> reg_exp T -> Prop :=
  | MEmpty : [] =~ EmptyStr
  | MChar x : [x] =~ (Char x)
  | MApp s1 re1 s2 re2
             (H1 : s1 =~ re1)
             (H2 : s2 =~ re2)
           : (s1 ++ s2) =~ (App re1 re2)
  | MUnionL s1 re1 re2
                (H1 : s1 =~ re1)
              : s1 =~ (Union re1 re2)
  | MUnionR s2 re1 re2
                (H2 : s2 =~ re2)
              : s2 =~ (Union re1 re2)
  | MStar0 re : [] =~ (Star re)
  | MStarApp s1 s2 re
                 (H1 : s1 =~ re)
                 (H2 : s2 =~ (Star re))
               : (s1 ++ s2) =~ (Star re)
Label: exp_match

  | App EmptyStr re2 => re_opt re2
  | App re1 EmptyStr => re_opt re1

  | Star EmptySet => EmptyStr
  | Star EmptyStr => EmptyStr
  | Star re => Star (re_opt re)
  | EmptySet => EmptySet
  | EmptyStr => EmptyStr
  | Char x => Char x
  end.

                                 (x : string) (vx : A),

Proof.
  unfold includedin.
  intros A m m' x vx H.
  intros y vy.
  destruct (eqb_spec x y) as [Hxy | Hxy].

 rewrite Hxy.
    rewrite update_eq.
rewrite update_eq.
intro H1.
apply H1.
  -
 rewrite update_neq.
    +
 rewrite update_neq.
      *
 apply H.
      *
 apply Hxy.
    +
 apply Hxy.
Qed.

Fixpoint beval (b : bexp) : bool :=
  match b with
  | BTrue       => true
  | BFalse      => false
  | BEq a1 a2   => (aeval a1) =? (aeval a2)
  | BNeq a1 a2  => negb ((aeval a1) =? (aeval a2))
  | BLe a1 a2   => (aeval a1) <=? (aeval a2)
  | BGt a1 a2   => negb ((aeval a1) <=? (aeval a2))
  | BNot b1     => negb (beval b1)
  | BAnd b1 b2  => andb (beval b1) (beval b2)
  end.

               (a : aexp) : nat :=
  match a with
  | ANum n => n
  | AId x => st x
  | <{a1 + a2}> => (aeval st a1) + (aeval st a2)
  | <{a1 - a2}> => (aeval st a1) - (aeval st a2)
  | <{a1 * a2}> => (aeval st a1) * (aeval st a2)
  end.

raw:
Fixpoint beval (st : state)
               (b : bexp) : bool :=
  match b with
  | <{true}>      => true
  | <{false}>     => false
  | <{a1 = a2}>   => (aeval st a1) =? (aeval st a2)
  | <{a1 <> a2}>  => negb ((aeval st a1) =? (aeval st a2))
  | <{a1 <= a2}>  => (aeval st a1) <=? (aeval st a2)
  | <{a1 > a2}>   => negb ((aeval st a1) <=? (aeval st a2))
  | <{~ b1}>      => negb (beval st b1)
  | <{b1 && b2}>  => andb (beval st b1) (beval st b2)
  end.
Label: beval

raw:
Fixpoint ceval_fun_no_while (st : state) (c : com) : state :=
  match c with
    | <{ skip }> =>
        st
    | <{ x := a }> =>
        (x !-> (aeval st a) ; st)
    | <{ c1 ; c2 }> =>
        let st' := ceval_fun_no_while st c1 in
        ceval_fun_no_while st' c2
    | <{ if b then c1 else c2 end}> =>
        if (beval st b)
          then ceval_fun_no_while st c1
          else ceval_fun_no_while st c2
    | <{ while b do c end }> =>
        st
  end.
Label: ceval_fun_no_while

Inductive ceval : com -> state -> state -> Prop :=
  | E_Skip : forall st,
      st =[ skip ]=> st
  | E_Asgn  : forall st a n x,
      aeval st a = n ->
      st =[ x := a ]=> (x !-> n ; st)
  | E_Seq : forall c1 c2 st st' st'',
      st  =[ c1 ]=> st'  ->
      st' =[ c2 ]=> st'' ->
      st  =[ c1 ; c2 ]=> st''
  | E_IfTrue : forall st st' b c1 c2,
      beval st b = true ->
      st =[ c1 ]=> st' ->
      st =[ if b then c1 else c2 end]=> st'
  | E_IfFalse : forall st st' b c1 c2,
      beval st b = false ->
      st =[ c2 ]=> st' ->
      st =[ if b then c1 else c2 end]=> st'
  | E_WhileFalse : forall b st c,
      beval st b = false ->
      st =[ while b do c end ]=> st
  | E_WhileTrue : forall st st' st'' b c,
      beval st b = true ->
      st  =[ c ]=> st' ->
      st' =[ while b do c end ]=> st'' ->
      st  =[ while b do c end ]=> st''
Label: ceval

  ~(st =[ loop ]=> st').

  intros st st' contra.
unfold loop in contra.
  remember <{ while true do skip end }> as loopdef
           eqn:Heqloopdef.

Fixpoint no_whiles (c : com) : bool :=
  match c with
  | <{ skip }> =>
      true
  | <{ _ := _ }> =>
      true
  | <{ c1 ; c2 }> =>
      andb (no_whiles c1) (no_whiles c2)
  | <{ if _ then ct else cf end }> =>
      andb (no_whiles ct) (no_whiles cf)
  | <{ while _ do _ end }>  =>
      false
  end.
Label: no_whiles

Inductive ceval : com -> state -> state -> Prop :=
  | E_Skip : forall st,
      st =[ skip ]=> st
  | E_Asgn  : forall st a1 n x,
      aeval st a1 = n ->
      st =[ x := a1 ]=> (x !-> n ; st)
  | E_Seq : forall c1 c2 st st' st'',
      st  =[ c1 ]=> st'  ->
      st' =[ c2 ]=> st'' ->
      st  =[ c1 ; c2 ]=> st''
  | E_IfTrue : forall st st' b c1 c2,
      beval st b = true ->
      st =[ c1 ]=> st' ->
      st =[ if b then c1 else c2 end ]=> st'
  | E_IfFalse : forall st st' b c1 c2,
      beval st b = false ->
      st =[ c2 ]=> st' ->
      st =[ if b then c1 else c2 end ]=> st'
  | E_WhileFalse : forall b st c,
      beval st b = false ->
      st =[ while b do c end ]=> st
  | E_WhileTrue : forall st st' st'' b c,
      beval st b = true ->
      st  =[ c ]=> st' ->
      st' =[ while b do c end ]=> st'' ->
      st  =[ while b do c end ]=> st''
  | E_RepeatEnd : forall st st' b c,
      st  =[ c ]=> st' ->
      beval st' b = true ->
      st  =[ repeat c until b end ]=> st'
  | E_RepeatLoop : forall st st' st'' b c,
      st  =[ c ]=> st' ->
      beval st' b = false ->
      st' =[ repeat c until b end ]=> st'' ->
      st  =[ repeat c until b end ]=> st''
Label: ceval

  (exists y, P 42 y) ->
  (forall x y : nat, P x y -> Q x) ->

Fixpoint ceval_step1 (st : state) (c : com) : state :=
  match c with
    | <{ skip }> =>
        st
    | <{ l := a1 }> =>
        (l !-> aeval st a1 ; st)
    | <{ c1 ; c2 }> =>
        let st' := ceval_step1 st c1 in
        ceval_step1 st' c2
    | <{ if b then c1 else c2 end }> =>
        if (beval st b)
          then ceval_step1 st c1
          else ceval_step1 st c2
    | <{ while b1 do c1 end }> =>
        st
  end.
Label: ceval_step1

raw:
Fixpoint ceval_step2 (st : state) (c : com) (i : nat) : state :=
  match i with
  | O => empty_st
  | S i' =>
    match c with
      | <{ skip }> =>
          st
      | <{ l := a1 }> =>
          (l !-> aeval st a1 ; st)
      | <{ c1 ; c2 }> =>
          let st' := ceval_step2 st c1 i' in
          ceval_step2 st' c2 i'
      | <{ if b then c1 else c2 end }> =>
          if (beval st b)
            then ceval_step2 st c1 i'
            else ceval_step2 st c2 i'
      | <{ while b1 do c1 end }> =>
          if (beval st b1)
          then let st' := ceval_step2 st c1 i' in
               ceval_step2 st' c i'
          else st
    end
  end.
Label: ceval_step2

raw:
Fixpoint ceval_step3 (st : state) (c : com) (i : nat)
                    : option state :=
  match i with
  | O => None
  | S i' =>
    match c with
      | <{ skip }> =>
          Some st
      | <{ l := a1 }> =>
          Some (l !-> aeval st a1 ; st)
      | <{ c1 ; c2 }> =>
          match (ceval_step3 st c1 i') with
          | Some st' => ceval_step3 st' c2 i'
          | None => None
          end
      | <{ if b then c1 else c2 end }> =>
          if (beval st b)
            then ceval_step3 st c1 i'
            else ceval_step3 st c2 i'
      | <{ while b1 do c1 end }> =>
          if (beval st b1)
          then match (ceval_step3 st c1 i') with
               | Some st' => ceval_step3 st' c i'
               | None => None
               end
          else Some st
    end
  end.
Label: ceval_step3

          Some st
      | <{ l := a1 }> =>
          Some (l !-> aeval st a1 ; st)
      | <{ c1 ; c2 }> =>
          LETOPT st' <== ceval_step st c1 i' IN
          ceval_step st' c2 i'
      | <{ if b then c1 else c2 end }> =>
          if (beval st b)
            then ceval_step st c1 i'
            else ceval_step st c2 i'
      | <{ while b1 do c1 end }> =>
          if (beval st b1)
          then LETOPT st' <== ceval_step st c1 i' IN
               ceval_step st' c i'
          else Some st
    end
  end.
Label: ceval_step

Theorem ceval_deterministic' : forall c st st1 st2,
     st =[ c ]=> st1 ->
     st =[ c ]=> st2 ->
     st1 = st2.
Proof.
  intros c st st1 st2 He1 He2.
  apply ceval__ceval_step in He1.
  apply ceval__ceval_step in He2.
  inversion He1 as [i1 E1].
  inversion He2 as [i2 E2].
  apply ceval_step_more with (i2 := i1 + i2) in E1.
  apply ceval_step_more with (i2 := i1 + i2) in E2.
  rewrite E1 in E2.
inversion E2.
reflexivity.
  lia.
lia.
 Qed.
Label: ceval_deterministic'

Definition isWhite (c : ascii) : bool :=
  let n := nat_of_ascii c in
  orb (orb (n =? 32)
           (n =? 9))
      (orb (n =? 10)
           (n =? 13)).
Label: isWhite

raw:
Notation "x '<=?' y" := (x <=? y)
  (at level 70, no associativity) : nat_scope.
Label: "x

raw:
Definition isLowerAlpha (c : ascii) : bool :=
  let n := nat_of_ascii c in
    andb (97 <=? n) (n <=? 122).
Label: isLowerAlpha

raw:
Definition isAlpha (c : ascii) : bool :=
  let n := nat_of_ascii c in
    orb (andb (65 <=? n) (n <=? 90))
        (andb (97 <=? n) (n <=? 122)).
Label: isAlpha

raw:
Definition isDigit (c : ascii) : bool :=
  let n := nat_of_ascii c in
     andb (48 <=? n) (n <=? 57).
Label: isDigit

raw: Inductive chartype := white | alpha | digit | other.
Label: chartype

raw:
Definition classifyChar (c : ascii) : chartype :=
  if isWhite c then
    white
  else if isAlpha c then
    alpha
  else if isDigit c then
    digit
  else
    other.
Label: classifyChar

raw:
Fixpoint list_of_string (s : string) : list ascii :=
  match s with
  | EmptyString => []
  | String c s => c :: (list_of_string s)
  end.
Label: list_of_string

raw:
Definition string_of_list (xs : list ascii) : string :=
  fold_right String EmptyString xs.
Label: string_of_list

raw: Definition token := string.
Label: token

raw:
Fixpoint tokenize_helper (cls : chartype) (acc xs : list ascii)
                       : list (list ascii) :=
  let tk := match acc with [] => [] | _::_ => [rev acc] end in
  match xs with
  | [] => tk
  | (x::xs') =>
    match cls, classifyChar x, x with
    | _, _, "("      =>
      tk ++ ["("]::(tokenize_helper other [] xs')
    | _, _, ")"      =>
      tk ++ [")"]::(tokenize_helper other [] xs')
    | _, white, _    =>
      tk ++ (tokenize_helper white [] xs')
    | alpha,alpha,x  =>
      tokenize_helper alpha (x::acc) xs'
    | digit,digit,x  =>
      tokenize_helper digit (x::acc) xs'
    | other,other,x  =>
      tokenize_helper other (x::acc) xs'
    | _,tp,x         =>
      tk ++ (tokenize_helper tp [x] xs')
    end
  end %char.
Label: tokenize_helper

raw:
Definition tokenize (s : string) : list string :=
  map string_of_list (tokenize_helper white [] (list_of_string s)).
Label: tokenize

Inductive optionE (X:Type) : Type :=
  | SomeE (x : X)
  | NoneE (s : string).

raw:
Notation "' p <- e1 ;; e2"
   := (match e1 with
       | SomeE p => e2
       | NoneE err => NoneE err
       end)
   (right associativity, p pattern, at level 60, e1 at next level).

Notation "'TRY' e1 'OR' e2"
   := (
    let result := e1 in
    match result with
       | SomeE _  => result
       | NoneE _ => e2
       end)
   (right associativity,
    at level 60, e1 at next level, e2 at next level).
Label: "'TRY'

raw:
Definition parser (T : Type) :=
  list token -> optionE (T * list token).
Label: parser

raw:
Fixpoint many_helper {T} (p : parser T) acc steps xs :=
  match steps, p xs with
  | 0, _ =>
      NoneE "Too many recursive calls"
  | _, NoneE _ =>
      SomeE ((rev acc), xs)
  | S steps', SomeE (t, xs') =>
      many_helper p (t :: acc) steps' xs'
  end.
Label: many_helper

raw:
Definition many {T} (p : parser T) (steps : nat) : parser (list T) :=
  many_helper p [] steps.
Label: many

raw:
Definition firstExpect {T} (t : token) (p : parser T)
                     : parser T :=
  fun xs => match xs with
            | x::xs' =>
              if string_dec x t
              then p xs'
              else NoneE ("expected '" ++ t ++ "'.")
            | [] =>
              NoneE ("expected '" ++ t ++ "'.")
            end.
Label: firstExpect

raw:
Definition expect (t : token) : parser unit :=
  firstExpect t (fun xs => SomeE (tt, xs)).
Label: expect

raw:
Definition parseIdentifier (xs : list token)
                         : optionE (string * list token) :=
match xs with
| [] => NoneE "Expected identifier"
| x::xs' =>
    if forallb isLowerAlpha (list_of_string x) then
      SomeE (x, xs')
    else
      NoneE ("Illegal identifier:'" ++ x ++ "'")
end.
Label: parseIdentifier

raw:
Definition parseNumber (xs : list token)
                     : optionE (nat * list token) :=
match xs with
| [] => NoneE "Expected number"
| x::xs' =>
    if forallb isDigit (list_of_string x) then
      SomeE (fold_left
               (fun n d =>
                  10 * n + (nat_of_ascii d -
                            nat_of_ascii "0"%char))
               (list_of_string x)
               0,
             xs')
    else
      NoneE "Expected number"
end.
Label: parseNumber

raw:
Fixpoint parsePrimaryExp (steps:nat)
                         (xs : list token)
                       : optionE (aexp * list token) :=
  match steps with
  | 0 => NoneE "Too many recursive calls"
  | S steps' =>
      TRY ' (i, rest) <- parseIdentifier xs ;;
          SomeE (AId i, rest)
      OR
      TRY ' (n, rest) <- parseNumber xs ;;
          SomeE (ANum n, rest)
      OR
      ' (e, rest) <- firstExpect "(" (parseSumExp steps') xs ;;
      ' (u, rest') <- expect ")" rest ;;
      SomeE (e,rest')
  end
Label: parsePrimaryExp

raw:
with parseProductExp (steps:nat)
                     (xs : list token) :=
  match steps with
  | 0 => NoneE "Too many recursive calls"
  | S steps' =>
    ' (e, rest) <- parsePrimaryExp steps' xs ;;
    ' (es, rest') <- many (firstExpect "*" (parsePrimaryExp steps'))
                          steps' rest ;;
    SomeE (fold_left AMult es e, rest')
  end
Label: parseProductExp

raw:
with parseSumExp (steps:nat) (xs : list token)  :=
  match steps with
  | 0 => NoneE "Too many recursive calls"
  | S steps' =>
    ' (e, rest) <- parseProductExp steps' xs ;;
    ' (es, rest') <-
        many (fun xs =>
                TRY ' (e,rest') <-
                    firstExpect "+"
                                (parseProductExp steps') xs ;;
                    SomeE ( (true, e), rest')
                OR
                ' (e, rest') <-
                    firstExpect "-"
                                (parseProductExp steps') xs ;;
                SomeE ( (false, e), rest'))
        steps' rest ;;
      SomeE (fold_left (fun e0 term =>
                          match term with
                          | (true,  e) => APlus e0 e
                          | (false, e) => AMinus e0 e
                          end)
                       es e,
             rest')
  end.
Label: parseSumExp

raw: Definition parseAExp := parseSumExp.
Label: parseAExp

raw:
Fixpoint parseAtomicExp (steps:nat)
                        (xs : list token)  :=
match steps with
  | 0 => NoneE "Too many recursive calls"
  | S steps' =>
     TRY ' (u,rest) <- expect "true" xs ;;
         SomeE (BTrue,rest)
     OR
     TRY ' (u,rest) <- expect "false" xs ;;
         SomeE (BFalse,rest)
     OR
     TRY ' (e,rest) <- firstExpect "~"
                                   (parseAtomicExp steps')
                                   xs ;;
         SomeE (BNot e, rest)
     OR
     TRY ' (e,rest) <- firstExpect "("
                                   (parseConjunctionExp steps')
                                   xs ;;
         ' (u,rest') <- expect ")" rest ;;
         SomeE (e, rest')
     OR
     ' (e, rest) <- parseProductExp steps' xs ;;
     TRY ' (e', rest') <- firstExpect "="
                                  (parseAExp steps') rest ;;
         SomeE (BEq e e', rest')
     OR
     TRY ' (e', rest') <- firstExpect "<="
                                      (parseAExp steps') rest ;;
         SomeE (BLe e e', rest')
     OR
     NoneE "Expected '=' or '<=' after arithmetic expression"
end
Label: parseAtomicExp

raw:
with parseConjunctionExp (steps:nat)
                         (xs : list token) :=
  match steps with
  | 0 => NoneE "Too many recursive calls"
  | S steps' =>
    ' (e, rest) <- parseAtomicExp steps' xs ;;
    ' (es, rest') <- many (firstExpect "&&"
               (parseAtomicExp steps'))
            steps' rest ;;
    SomeE (fold_left BAnd es e, rest')
  end.
Label: parseConjunctionExp

raw: Definition parseBExp := parseConjunctionExp.
Label: parseBExp

raw: Check parseConjunctionExp.
Label: parseConjunctionExp.

raw:
Fixpoint parseSimpleCommand (steps:nat)
                            (xs : list token) :=
  match steps with
  | 0 => NoneE "Too many recursive calls"
  | S steps' =>
    TRY ' (u, rest) <- expect "skip" xs ;;
        SomeE (<{skip}>, rest)
    OR
    TRY ' (e,rest) <-
            firstExpect "if"
                        (parseBExp steps') xs ;;
        ' (c,rest') <-
            firstExpect "then"
                        (parseSequencedCommand steps') rest ;;
        ' (c',rest'') <-
            firstExpect "else"
                        (parseSequencedCommand steps') rest' ;;
        ' (tt,rest''') <-
            expect "end" rest'' ;;
       SomeE(<{if e then c else c' end}>, rest''')
    OR
    TRY ' (e,rest) <-
            firstExpect "while"
                        (parseBExp steps') xs ;;
        ' (c,rest') <-
            firstExpect "do"
                        (parseSequencedCommand steps') rest ;;
        ' (u,rest'') <-
            expect "end" rest' ;;
        SomeE(<{while e do c end}>, rest'')
    OR
    TRY ' (i, rest) <- parseIdentifier xs ;;
        ' (e, rest') <- firstExpect ":=" (parseAExp steps') rest ;;
        SomeE (<{i := e}>, rest')
    OR
        NoneE "Expecting a command"
end
Label: parseSimpleCommand

raw:
with parseSequencedCommand (steps:nat)
                           (xs : list token) :=
  match steps with
  | 0 => NoneE "Too many recursive calls"
  | S steps' =>
    ' (c, rest) <- parseSimpleCommand steps' xs ;;
    TRY ' (c', rest') <-
            firstExpect ";"
                        (parseSequencedCommand steps') rest ;;
        SomeE (<{c ; c'}>, rest')
    OR
    SomeE (c, rest)
  end.
Label: parseSequencedCommand

raw: Definition bignumber := 1000.
Label: bignumber

raw:
Definition parse (str : string) : optionE com :=
  let tokens := tokenize str in
  match parseSequencedCommand bignumber tokens with
  | SomeE (c, []) => SomeE c
  | SomeE (_, t::_) => NoneE ("Trailing tokens remaining: " ++ t)
  | NoneE err => NoneE err
  end.
Label: parse

Definition partial_function {X: Type} (R: relation X) :=
  forall x y1 y2 : X, R x y1 -> R x y2 -> y1 = y2.
Label: partial_function

raw:
Inductive next_nat : nat -> nat -> Prop :=
  | nn n : next_nat n (S n).
Label: next_nat

raw: Check next_nat : relation nat.
Label: next_nat

raw:
Theorem next_nat_partial_function :
  partial_function next_nat.
Proof.
  unfold partial_function.
  intros x y1 y2 H1 H2.
  inversion H1.
inversion H2.
  reflexivity.
 Qed.
Label: next_nat_partial_function

raw:
Theorem le_not_a_partial_function :
  ~ (partial_function le).
Proof.
  unfold not.
unfold partial_function.
intros Hc.
  assert (0 = 1) as Nonsense.
{
    apply Hc with (x := 0).
    -
 apply le_n.
    -
 apply le_S.
apply le_n.
}
  discriminate Nonsense.
  Qed.
Label: le_not_a_partial_function

Definition reflexive {X: Type} (R: relation X) :=
  forall a : X, R a a.
Label: reflexive

raw:
Theorem le_reflexive :
  reflexive le.
Proof.
  unfold reflexive.
intros n.
apply le_n.
 Qed.
Label: le_reflexive

raw:
Definition transitive {X: Type} (R: relation X) :=
  forall a b c : X, (R a b) -> (R b c) -> (R a c).
Label: transitive

raw:
Theorem le_trans :
  transitive le.
Proof.
  intros n m o Hnm Hmo.

apply IHHmo.

   Admitted.

raw:
Ltac check_type A B :=
    match type of A with
    | context[MISSING] => idtac "Missing:" A
    | ?T => first [unify T B; idtac "Type: ok" | idtac "Type: wrong - should be (" B ")"]
    end.

raw:
Ltac print_manual_grade A :=
    match eval compute in A with
    | Some (_ ?S ?C) =>
        idtac "Score:"  S;
        match eval compute in C with
          | ""%string => idtac "Comment: None"
          | _ => idtac "Comment:" C
        end
    | None =>
        idtac "Score: Ungraded";
        idtac "Comment: None"
    end.
Label: print_manual_grade
